==English==
===Etymology===
Prefix a- (for of) + [[kin]].

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ʌˈkɪn/

===Adjective===
# Of the same kin; related by blood;&mdash;used of persons; as, the two families are near akin.
# Allied by nature; partaking of the same properties; of the same kind.
#:    The literary character of the work is akin to its moral character. --Jeffrey.
#:    Note: This adjective is used only after the noun.